  "examTip": "8051 is a 40-pin DIP microcontroller. Port 0 (pins 32-39) is a multiplexed address/data bus (AD0-AD7). Port 2 (pins 21-28) outputs high byte of address (A8-A15). Port 1 (pins 1-8) is a general-purpose I/O port. Port 3 (pins 10-17) has dual functions including RXD, TXD, INT0, INT1, T0, T1, WR, RD.",
